   =20
      Is 420 a weed joke?
   =20
 =20

In August 2018,   Elon Musk tweeted that he was =E2=80=9Cconsidering taking=
 Tesla private at $420. Funding secured.=E2=80=9D   Funding was not secured=
, Tesla did not go private, and Musk was sued for fraud both   by the US Se=
curities and Exchange Commission and by a class of investors who traded Tes=
la shares based on that tweet. Musk quickly   settled with the SEC, but the=
 class action dragged on. There is now a jury trial in California, and Musk=
  has been testifying=C2=A0Friday, Monday and today.
Here is a paragraph of  the 2018 SEC complaint that I have quoted before:
According to Musk, he calculated the $420 price per share based on a 20% pr=
emium over that day=E2=80=99s closing share price because he thought 20% wa=
s a =E2=80=9Cstandard premium=E2=80=9D in going-private transactions. This =
calculation resulted in a price of $419, and Musk stated that=C2=A0he round=
ed the price up to $420 because he had recently learned about the number=E2=
=80=99s significance in marijuana culture and thought his girlfriend =E2=80=
=9Cwould find it funny, which admittedly is not a great reason to pick a pr=
ice.=E2=80=9D
It occurs to me now that I do not know what those quotation marks mean. The=
 SEC does=C2=A0not seem to be quoting any of Musk=E2=80=99s public statemen=
ts or tweets about the deal. I always assumed that the SEC conducted an inv=
estigation in which it interviewed Musk, and these statements are from that=
 interview, and somewhere the SEC has a videotape or at least an official t=
ranscript=C2=A0of Musk explaining that 420 is a weed joke. But the complain=
t doesn=E2=80=99t actually=C2=A0say=C2=A0that, and perhaps I=E2=80=99m wron=
g. Perhaps the SEC interviewed somebody involved in the deal =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0Musk=E2=80=99s friend or banker or financing source or girlfriend =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and that person remembered Musk saying that and the SEC quoted it =
secondhand.=C2=A0
Anyway, Musk later bought Twitter Inc. for $54.20 per share, and I have spe=
nt the last four and a half years  occasionally saying =E2=80=9C420 is a we=
ed joke=E2=80=9D in the context of Elon Musk=E2=80=99s financial activities=
, and yesterday I learned that it =E2=80=A6=C2=A0maybe =E2=80=A6=C2=A0isn=
=E2=80=99t?  This blew my mind:
Musk told the jury that the proposed $420 per share price to take Tesla pri=
vate was, =E2=80=9Cnot a joke,=E2=80=9D and said any connections between it=
 and references to marijuana tropes were purely a coincidence.=C2=A0
What.  And:

Musk acknowledged that the actual Tesla stock price after adding a 20% prem=
ium totaled $419 and more than 50 cents, and explained that he rounded the =
number up to $420. It was "a coincidence," he said. Pressed by the plaintif=
f's lawyer about whether he believed his "girlfriend"=E2=80=94presumably th=
e famous DJ Claire Elise Boucher, otherwise known as Grimes, with whom Musk=
 has two children=E2=80=94"would find it funny," Musk said he wasn't sure.
"I don't know if she found it funny or not. But the 420 price was not a jok=
e," Musk said.
"There is some karma around 420," Musk noted moments later, "although I sho=
uld question if that is good or bad karma at this point.=E2=80=9D

What. What. Look, again, my assumption was always that the SEC has a videot=
ape of Musk saying it was a weed joke. Perhaps I am wrong. But what if I=E2=
=80=99m right! If you are a plaintiffs=E2=80=99=C2=A0lawyer in this case, y=
ou had better be calling the SEC for that videotape. If you are the SEC =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0and the SEC has taken a lot of abuse from Musk in recent years =
and wouldn=E2=80=99t mind sticking it to him a bit=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0you =
had better be calling the plaintiffs=E2=80=99 lawyers and offering it to th=
em. Frankly if you are the SEC you ought to clip that videotape and email i=
t to me to publish in this newsletter! Honestly what is this newsletter for=
 if not to litigate whether Elon Musk=E2=80=99s habit of buying, or   prete=
nding to buy, companies for prices that involve the number =E2=80=9C420=E2=
=80=9D is a weed joke?
By the way, I=E2=80=99ve   said this before, but as a price $420 seems tota=
lly reasonable (and frankly cheap given Tesla=E2=80=99s subsequent performa=
nce
  [1]
), and Musk=E2=80=99s process of taking the closing price, adding 20%, and =
rounding to a pleasing number is just fine. If I were on the jury, my decis=
ion about whether or not Musk did securities fraud would not really be affe=
cted by whether the price was a weed joke. But as a citizen and a financial=
 columnist, I need to know whether it was a weed joke.

