rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the 2018 SEC complaint</a> that I have quo=
ted before:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to Musk, he calculated t=
he $420 price per share based on a 20% premium over that day=E2=80=99s clos=
ing share price because he thought 20% was a =E2=80=9Cstandard premium=E2=
=80=9D in going-private transactions. This calculation resulted in a price =
of $419, and Musk stated that=C2=A0he rounded the price up to $420 because =
he had recently learned about the number=E2=80=99s significance in marijuan=
a culture and thought his girlfriend =E2=80=9Cwould find it funny, which ad=
mittedly is not a great reason to pick a price.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It occurs to me now that I do not know what th=
ose quotation marks mean. The SEC does=C2=A0not seem to be quoting any of M=
usk=E2=80=99s public statements or tweets about the deal. I always assumed =
that the SEC conducted an investigation in which it interviewed Musk, and t=
hese statements are from that interview, and somewhere the SEC has a videot=
ape or at least an official transcript=C2=A0of Musk explaining that 420 is =
a weed joke. But the complaint doesn=E2=80=99t actually=C2=A0<em>say=C2=A0<=
/em>that, and perhaps I=E2=80=99m wrong. Perhaps the SEC interviewed somebo=
dy involved in the deal =E2=80=94=C2=A0Musk=E2=80=99s friend or banker or f=
inancing source or girlfriend =E2=80=94=C2=A0and that person remembered Mus=
k saying that and the SEC quoted it secondhand.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, Musk later bought Twitter Inc. for $54=
.20 per share, and I have spent the last four and a half years <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30347296.266447/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3=
cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS9zZWFyY2g_cT1tYXR0K2xldmluZSslMjI0MjAraXMrYSt3ZWVkK2pva2UlM=
jI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB377b0326" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> occasionally saying</a> =E2=
=80=9C420 is a weed joke=E2=80=9D in the context of Elon Musk=E2=80=99s fin=
ancial activities, and yesterday I learned that it =E2=80=A6=C2=A0maybe =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0isn=E2=80=99t? <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/30347296.266447/aHR0cHM6Ly9naXptb2RvLmNvbS9lbG9uLW11c2stdGVzbGEtdH=
