<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Funding secured</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The whole trial is very weird? The basic situa=
tion is that the judge <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/30347296.266447/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGl0LXNsLnNoZWFybWFuLmNvbS9zaXRlRmlsZX=
MvMzk3MTkvU0wyX0luJTIwUmUlMjBUZXNsYSwlMjBJbmMuJTIwU2VjLiUyMExpdGlnLi1tdXNrJ=
TIwb3JkZXIlMjB1bnNlYWxlZC5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf05e5c95" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 has already ruled</a> that Musk=E2=80=99s tweet that he had =E2=80=9Cfundi=
ng secured=E2=80=9D was false, and that he made this false statement reckle=
ssly. So the trial =E2=80=94=C2=A0in this lawsuit about whether Musk commit=
ted securities fraud =E2=80=94 is only for the jury to whether his tweets w=
ere material to investors, whether they relied on those tweets, stuff like =
that. Those strike me as somewhat technical questions of securities class a=
ction law that would be hard and annoying for a jury to decide, whereas it =
would be reasonable to ask a jury =E2=80=9Cwell, did he have funding secure=
d, or what?=E2=80=9D But the actual trial is the opposite: The jury rules o=
n questions of materiality, but the question of whether Musk=E2=80=99s twee=
ts were false is already settled.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footn=
ote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !i=
mportant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;"=
>
<span>[2]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Reasonably, nobody is acting like that, and Mu=
sk testified that he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/30347296.266447/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9lbG9uLW11c2staGVh=
ZGVkLWJhY2stdG8tY291cnQtb3Zlci10ZXNsYS10d2VldHMtMTE2NzQ0ODA3ODQ_bW9kPWl0cF9=
3c2omcnU9eWFob28/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBec8413ae" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> really did hav=
e funding secured</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk said he had funding to take Tesla In=
c. private when he floated the idea in 2018, saying that financing from Sau=
di Arabia=E2=80=99s sovereign-wealth fund and his own stake in rocket-compa=
ny SpaceX would have provided sufficient capital.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWith the SpaceX stock alone, I felt f=
unding was secured,=E2=80=9D Mr. Musk said Monday in his second day on the =
stand in a case brought by investors who say they lost money because of his=
 tweets proposing to take the car company private.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Musk met with representatives of Saudi Ara=
bia=E2=80=99s sovereign-wealth fund, the Public Investment Fund, in late Ju=
ly 2018, a week before floating the possibility of taking Tesla private. A =
specific price for taking Tesla private wasn=E2=80=99t discussed at that me=
eting, nor was there a signed document, Mr. Musk testified. Nevertheless, M=
r. Musk said he walked away from the meeting thinking it was a =E2=80=9Cdon=
e deal.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe thing that was really, absolutely=
 unequivocal was that they were absolutely supportive of taking Tesla priva=
te,=E2=80=9D he said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look, we all <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/30347296.266447/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDgtMTMvZnVuZGluZy1mb3ItZWxvbi1tdXNrLXMtdGVzbG=
EtYnV5b3V0LXdhc24tdC1zby1zZWN1cmU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX=
21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMTI0JnV0bV9j=
YW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6eeb0280" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  made =
fun of this</a> at the time, and certainly=C2=A0<em>I=C2=A0</em>would not s=
ay that I had funding secured if I hadn=E2=80=99t discussed=C2=A0<em>the am=
ount of funding or the price=C2=A0</em>with my financing source. I=E2=80=99=
m not really going to=C2=A0<em>disagree=C2=A0</em>with the judge=E2=80=99s,=
 and the SEC=E2=80=99s, conclusion that the =E2=80=9Cfunding secured=E2=80=
=9D claim was false.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I will say, though, that I had the same reacti=
on to Musk=E2=80=99s plans to take Twitter Inc. private last year. When he =
proposed to buy Twitter, back in April, I wrote a column titled =E2=80=9C<a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30347296.266447/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTUvc3VyZS1=
lbG9uLW11c2stbWlnaHQtYnV5LXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdX=
RtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMTI0JnV0b=
V9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb74e8f65" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Sure=
 Elon Musk Might Buy Twitter</a>,=E2=80=9D saying:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I imagine that=C2=A0Twitter's bank=
ers at Goldman Sachs will sit down with Musk's bankers at Morgan Stanley an=
d Goldman will say =E2=80=9Cso uh where's the financing coming from=E2=80=
=9D and Morgan Stanley will say =E2=80=9Coh the financing is in this can=E2=
=80=9D and hand Goldman a can and Goldman will open the can and a bunch of =
fake snakes will pop out. =E2=80=9CAAAHHH,=E2=80=9D Goldman will scream, an=
d then they will chuckle and=C2=A0say =E2=80=9Coh Elon, you got us again=E2=
=80=9D and everyone will have a good laugh. Because, again, uniquely among =
public-company CEOs, Elon Musk has in the past pretended he was going to ta=
ke a public company private with pretend financing! I am not saying that he=
=E2=80=99s joking now; I am just saying he=E2=80=99s the only person who ha=
s ever made this particular joke in the past.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/30347296.266447/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGl=
uaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjEvZWxvbi1nb3QtaGlzLW1vbmV5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMj=
QyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0b=
V90ZXJtPTIzMDEyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
5e23935c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">  like a=C2=A0week later</a> Musk showed up with signed c=
ommitment letters for $46.5 billion in financing, with roughly half of it c=
oming from his own personal wealth and the rest coming from reputable banks=
. And then he really did buy Twitter, for cash. Shows what I know! I still =
think he was joking in 2018, but he more or less was not joking in 2022, an=
d, you know, that=E2=80=99s a data point. Musk is very rich, has a lot of d=
evoted fans, and has a good track record of tapping them for money. If he w=
ants to spend a few tens of billions of dollars on something, he can probab=
ly find the money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That was much=C2=A0<em>less=C2=A0</em>true in =
2018 =E2=80=94=C2=A0when Tesla was worth about $60 billion (it was over $1 =
trillion when he started on Twitter, though it=E2=80=99s less now), when Mu=
sk was not the richest person in the world (as he was before Twitter though=
, again, not now), when SpaceX was not <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/30347296.266447/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZX=
dzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMTMvc3BhY2V4LXRlbmRlci1vZmZlci1pcy1zYWlkLXRvLXZhb=
HVlLWNvbXBhbnktYXQtMTQwLWJpbGxpb24tbGJsajJlMWY_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEyNDIzX01PTkVZ=
U1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjM=
wMTI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe4ba10a5" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">  worth $140 billion</a>, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0but even then, Musk was=
 already Musk. He was a pretty good pitchman. Could he have raised the $60 =
billion or so needed to take Tesla private? Maybe? Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30347296.266447/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2xpdmUtYmxvZy8yMDIzLTAxLTIwL2Vsb24tbXVza=
y1zZWN1cml0aWVzLXRyaWFsP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMjQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09=
ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDEyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ24=
9bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC10a2565c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Dana Hull repor=
ted</a> from his testimony yesterday:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk says he=E2=80=99s raised =E2=80=9Cmore mo=
ney than anyone in history by a significant margin=E2=80=9D because investo=
rs =E2=80=9Ctrust me to be truthful and responsible with their money.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk says he=E2=80=99s raised over $100 billio=
n in total.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And today:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk says that =E2=80=9Cevery fina=
ncing round I=E2=80=99ve ever done=E2=80=9D has been oversubscribed.=C2=A0<=
/p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, I do recall reading last month about a <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30347296.266447/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMTkvZWxvbi=
13YW50cy1zb21lLXR3aXR0ZXItaGVscD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTI0MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fb=
WVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAxMjQmdXRtX2Nh=
bXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB55c6152a" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  suppos=
ed financing round</a> at Musk=E2=80=99s newly private Twitter, where he wa=
s going to go out and raise money at the same $44 billion-ish valuation he =
agreed to in April. That seemed improbable, and I haven=E2=80=99t heard abo=
ut it since, suggesting that maybe it was not oversubscribed?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess this all has nothing really to do with=
 the lawsuit, since (1) he had not raised the financing to buy Twitter when=
 he tweeted that he had and (2) he never actually did. But really his posit=
ion is that he tweeted that he was=C2=A0<em>considering=C2=A0</em>taking Te=
sla private, and that if he=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>end up deciding to take =
it private then financing would not be a problem. We can=E2=80=99t really k=
now if that=E2=80=99s true, because the condition was never satisfied. But =
it seems like it might be.</p>
